						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">King: Rājakēśarivarmaṉ (Rājarāja I) Year 4: 989 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>Records the gift of sheep by Eṉādiyi Sūrāḍiyakaṇḍaṉ of Marudāḍu in Marudāḍunāḍu in Veṇkuṉṟa-kōṭṭam, to burn a lamp in the big temple of Marudāḍu. The donor entrusted the gift (sheep) to a shepherd, Mādēvaṉ, who agreed to measure out 5 <hi rend="italic">nāḻi</hi> annually for burning the lamp. </p>						

